; This is a sample file that causes city desk to automaticly download
; fonts to an HP LaserJet.
;
; All commands must start in column 1.  The following are valid commands:
;
R
; RESET: resets the printer and erases all fonts
;
;D <file> <id>
; DOWNLOAD: download softfont <file> and assign it id <id>
;
;X <file> <id> <font name> <size> <style>
; EXTENDED DOWNLOAD: same as 'D' command, but allows City Desk to switch
; fonts by specifing the font id of the font to use. <font name> is the
; name of the font you use to specify this font within City Desk.  <size>
; is the City Desk point size of the font you use when specifying this
; font.  Both <font name> and <size> should match the values used when
; creating the .hp file with the laser utility. <style> should be one of
; these numbers: 0 = plain, 1 = italic, 2 = bold, 8 = compressed
;
;  (the semicolun indicates a comment line)
;
R
X /texsf/cmr12.sf 1 cmr 12 0
X /texsf/cmrb12.sf 2 cmr 12 2
X /texsf/cmrb24.sf 3 cmr 24 2
;D trp10 1
;D trp10b 2
;X trp12 3 times 12 0
;D trp12b 4
;X trp18b 5 times 18 2
;D hlp12 6
;D hlp30b 7

